-== Duane - Cybersecurity ==-

Cybersecurity eludes to a user’s privacy and security on electronic devices such as mobiles and computers. There are many things that can be implemented to increase cyber security from notorious things on the internet such as viruses and spyware. Cybersecurity can refer to either the common countermeasures that users on the internet can use to increase their cyber security online. Another countermeasure to increase one’s cyber security would be using software to protect a device from malicious threats. One of the recommended software programs that a user can install would be Fidelis Deception. This software is designed to create false documents and files to lure hackers and other threats to them to protect the real data. This software is specifically designed to create convincing and legitimate looking decoy files as usually a threat may be able to tell the difference between a fake trail and a real trail that leads to the user’s data. 
However, there are quite a few people who would argue that the best security would be to know how to surf the internet in a proper and safe manner. Some extremely basic precautions when browsing the web would be to avoid any sketchy looking websites at all costs and to avoid viewing emails that are not from a trustworthy sender. Knowing how to use the internet in a appropriate manner can help avoid encountering any proper issues completely that it removes the need for an anti-virus software. 
In the future, as modern technology continues to evolve further and further, the impact technology has on our daily lives also continues to grow, thus the need for cybersecurity also drastically increases. Even today, cybersecurity has brought upon some debatable moments when referring to privacy. Facebook is an example of this. Facebook creator Mark Zuckerberg faced the US Congress due to a data-mining company named ‘Cambridge Analytica” who are affiliated with Donald Trump and using information from the privacy of 87 million Facebook users to influence elections. Obviously, this caused a major outrage from users of Facebook who directed their rage to Mark Zuckerberg, the founder of Facebook for his failure to prevent third parties from accessing their private data. This is a prime example of just how vital cybersecurity is on the internet, especially on popular social media platforms such as Facebook. 
Any data that is being transferred onto the internet in some form has a chance of being attacked or stolen by a malicious user or threat. Any technological advance that involves the internet nowadays, cybersecurity must meet to be able to protect it. Cybersecurity has been a thing for quite a while, even before the internet came into fruition. The military, government, private organizations and more used ‘private networks’ for their own uses. However, one of the first common security issues came when others needed to join a network. The network itself would have to be set to public so users can see and connect to it. This raised the main problem on how your network can truly be ‘private’ if everyone can see it. These cybersecurity issues will only continue to increase as technology evolves and malicious users continually try to find new ways to infiltrate your device or network for whatever reason. 
Cybersecurity must continue to evolve to protect the data of users on the internet as it evolves in the foreseeable future. The importance of cybersecurity will only grow as the internet and technology continues to be integrated into our daily lives. 


Cybersecurity has helped keep the privacy, key information and other kinds of files available to the right people only. However, these security measures are in place due to the potential hazards and dangers that the internet can create such as the sharing of information about people without their consent. An example of how letting out the private information of a user can have negative impacts is if someone chooses to commit fraud and pose as another user before committing a criminal act. Of course, increased cybersecurity will only lead to notorious hackers to scurry and find any potential holes in the security wall that has been set to infiltrate and get their hands on a user’s personal data such as credit card information. 
Cybersecurity can only go so far, as there is bound to be a method of some sort for others to infiltrate the system. Cybersecurity’s goal is to make it as hard as possible for potential threats to gain unauthorized access to the data. This can be done through various methods such as encryption. Encryption is a method of locking something behind a password of some kind before it can be properly accessed. Most companies use a common password set by their employees to safeguard each employee’s data to prevent others from accessing each other’s data. Much more advanced encryptions are used for more important data such as Facebook that uses encryption to protect the storage that stores user data provided through Facebook. Over the years, encryption has improved, making it harder and harder for people to decipher and decrypt certain keys to databases that stores all sorts of information. 
Cybersecurity will only continue to improve in the future as technology continues to progress through many technological stages. As technology gets better and better and more integrated into our lives, the importance of cybersecurity will increase further and further. However, this also means that cybersecurity will also have no choice but to increase its efficiency and effectiveness against all malicious threats. 
As cybersecurity continues to grow as part of the many technological advances that our society experiences. Practically every user of the internet will be affected by the many changed that come. Increased cybersecurity will mean that a user may have to insert more drastic countermeasures in the future to properly safeguard their information. Passwords used to be the most common encryptions on most devices, however now there are many other ways to lock a device or network without a specific ‘key’ of some sort to unlock it. Examples of these special encryption methods would be fingerprint scanners that many laptops and smartphones use to identify a user and thus grant that specific user access to the device. It’s possible that society will have to begin using similar types of encryption such as face recognition, fingerprint scanner, iris scanner, etc. to properly safeguard and ensure the safety of their data or device. 
Since technology continually advances and progressed every year, the need for increased and improved cybersecurity will also drastically increase. This results in a spike increase in demand of developers and programmers who can create better and better encryption and security method and software to prevent ill-natured users from infiltrating networks and devices and potentially cause harm. This will in turn, make past technologies and encryption methods redundant as society no longer needs them as it will possibly make their data too vulnerable to threats. This may lead to a loss of jobs of the people who do create these encryption and security methods that have become redundant. Although, it is likely they will find a new job or improve their current methods of security to be on par with other types of cybersecurity and to be able to defend against the many threats that will also evolve as technology evolves. 


The use of cybersecurity affects me in my everyday life in almost all the major devices that I use. My smartphone and my laptop contain encryption that is harder to be bypassed by other users such as a password. Although, my smartphone also uses a finger-print scanner as a method of checking security before granting access to the user of that device. It is extremely likely that cybersecurity will continue to be a thing in my everyday life as I live in a society that relies heavily on technology. It is equally as likely however, that I will have to change my methods of security in the future such as the passwords I use on my social media accounts incase my current password becomes too unreliable. 
In a modern society like my own that relies on technology as a part of our everyday lives, cybersecurity will always be a key factor in protecting all the data that we upload and download from the internet on a daily basis. My family and friends are not exempt from this. They too, use technology constantly, in work, school and for entertainment. Cybersecurity will be a key thing in all of our lives for likely the rest of our lives in protecting our privacy and data from harm. 

