-== Jacky - Robots ==-

What does it do? (600 words) What is the state of the art of this new technology? What can
be done now? What is likely to be able to do be done soon (say in the next 3 years)? What
technological or other developments make this possible?
Robots have always played a role in our lives, whether it for commercial use or business wise, robots and machinery has always made our lives easier. With new technology and invention being made to deal with modern problems, robots have been a part of the equation. While we can see that robots are used in everyday situation, robots are also used in other fields, from medical field to military, their role are endless. Most recently, the Da Vinci robot has made headline from social media with a video presenting a Da Vinci robot removing a grape skin and resewing the skin back. This demonstrates to the world that robots are capable of preforming operation in the medical field, being more beneficial than an actual doctor, with their “hands” being more precise and steadier than human doctors. However, robots lack one thing, a conscience, and because they might not understand what is going on at that moment, they could mess up or only do what its programmed to do, that is why robots are only used in smaller, minor situation. But in future time, with new programing or invention, robots may learn how to adapt in situation and preform in different condition. in the next coming years, advancements will be made to improve robots to be able to perform in those situations to make lives more easier for the user. Robots are likely to replace or help in though situation, for example, the recent news of the Notre Dame fire had enlisted the help of a recently built robot, “Colossus”, who was designed to be firefighting robot and was able to enter into the dangerous area and fight the devastating fire. The use of the robot was able to not only prevent innocent people to a dangerous area but also extinguishe the fire with its high-powered cannon without ever going back out. From this event and in the future, many developers will develop robots that will deal with jobs that are dangerous to humans. From these examples we can see that robots are capable to preforming jobs in hazardous condition while preforming pinpoint actions than actual human people. What makes this possible is the developers themselves. Developers have to make sure that the robot is built to solve that problems, and with modern problems appearing more, modern solution is the answer, and to make this happen, developers need to improve on “artificial intelligence”. If developers are able to improve or make developments on AI, the robots will not only be able to preform the task, but will ‘learn’ from it, and adapt from it, making robots the superior choice for that task.


What is the likely impact? (300 words) What is the potential impact of this development?
What is likely to change? Which people will be most affected and how? Will this create,
replace or make redundant any current jobs or technologies?

the impact of robots can be both positive and negative to the world. 
Some positive impact is that robots are that robots can improve on life qualities, making our lives easier. This can be already seen through SIRI from apple and Alexa from Amazon, which user use to store any information to it, giving more time for the user to do other things. For commercial use, robots are beneficial for everyday jobs that human will see as a bothersome and allow human more free time to do other task. Robots can also be used for dangerous situation, just like the last question, robots can be used as a replacement for humans to reduce the risk of lives, while also outperforming humans in their own jobs.
However, some negative things that robots may impact  is that robots can replace human jobs, replacing human resource to robots, giving less opportunity to humans. This will most likely impact anyone as their job could be replace by a robot, who could be better at performing their job than themselves. This would leave many people out of job and will make people furious about the situation and most likely turn against robots, who was made to make  people lives easier. 
How will this affect you? (300 words) In your daily life, how will this affect you? What
will be different for you? How might this affect members of your family or your friends?
For me personally, robots, in my daily life makes it easier for me. From when I wake up through the use of the phone alarm, to when I catch public transport to get to university or to when I do my school work through school computer/laptop, robots makes my life easier, doing task which I find bothersome. What makes it different for me is that robots has been around my life, it’s difficult to tell what task I’m have done and what was robots have done. How this affects my family and friends is that their use of robots, whether in phones or somewhere else, also benefits them, for example, my parents own a butcher shop in which a program is required to record any sales and money record that the shop makes, making my parents jobs easier and allowing them to focus on other things.


